articles.excerpt: Former ROH World Champions will address each other as Adam Cole is set to come face to face with Chris Jericho on this week's "AEW Dynamite."
articles.summary:
Adam Cole had some inspiring words for his AEW colleague Keith Lee last week, much to the chagrin of Lee's opponent Chris Jericho.


Adam Cole shared
 an announcement that Jericho and Cole will come face to face on this Wednesday's edition of "AEW Dynamite." The show will take place in Pittsburgh, PA. AEW 
shared a video
 from 
last week's "Dynamite,"

articles.title: Every Current Champion In AEW: Where Were They 10 Years Ago
articles.author: Kebin Antony
articles.excerpt: Find out where all the current champions in AEW were 10 years ago.
articles.summary:
All Elite Wrestling
 has one of the most star-studded rosters in the current pro wrestling industry. With wrestlers from all over the globe, Tony Khan's company has grown into the next biggest wrestling promotion in the world.
 
Tony Khan also acquired Ring of Honor in March 2022 and is running the promotion as a separate entity, but has the wrestlers from the ROH roster appear on AEW television as well.
 
There are fourteen championships across both sister promotions, with some of the best wrestlers representing them as champions.

articles.excerpt: Ahead of the second iteration of AEW and NJPW's Forbidden Door pay-per-view, a former WWE Superstar has named his ideal opponent for the show.
articles.summary:
Ahead of the second iteration of AEW and NJPW's Forbidden Door pay-per-view, a former WWE Superstar has named his ideal opponent for the show.

The star in question is former WWE Cruiserweight Champion Lio Rush. The Man of the Hour worked for AEW after being released from the world's largest wrestling promotion in April 2020. He is currently signed to New Japan, where he has quickly become a popular star in the company.

articles.title: Kevin Owens and Sami Zayn could lose titles if deadly duo reunites in WWE after 6 years
articles.author: Uday Maggon
articles.excerpt: Kevin Owens and Sami Zayn provided WWE fans with one of the greatest WrestleMania moments of the modern era at WrestleMania 39.
articles.summary:
Kevin Owens and Sami Zayn provided WWE fans with one of the greatest WrestleMania moments of the modern era at WrestleMania 39. The duo defeated arguably the greatest tag team of their generation, The Usos, and emerged victorious with the tag team titles. However, their reign could be under serious threat if Erick Redbeard returns to the company to reunite with Bray Wyatt.

Erick Redbeard was known as Erick Rowan during his time in the global wrestling juggernaut. He was a member of the Wyatt Family alongside Bray Wyatt and Luke Harper.

articles.title: There's only one Samoan who should take over The Bloodline from Roman Reigns
articles.author: Shubhajit Deb
articles.excerpt: The Bloodline leader, Roman Reigns, is seemingly running out of opponents to conquer in WWE.
articles.summary:
The Bloodline leader, Roman Reigns, is seemingly running out of opponents to conquer in WWE. Under the circumstances, there is a particular Samoan superstar that could credibly remove The Tribal Chief from the faction itself.

The star in question is none other than Samoa Joe. While the 44-year-old star is signed to AEW, he has only been seen in ROH matches over the last few weeks. He was released from WWE in 2021, although he did appear in NXT afterwards.

Samoa Joe has already stated that he was not interested in teaming up with Roman Reigns and The Usos on account of being grouped together simply because they were Samoan.

articles.title: WWE had "some interest" in signing 39-year-old AEW star
articles.author: Ojas Kulkarni
articles.excerpt: It has been reported that an AEW star has put rumors to rest by signing a new deal with the promotion.
articles.summary:
It has been reported that an AEW star has put rumors to rest by signing a new deal with the promotion. There were previous speculations that Brian Cage was unhappy with the company and was considering a move to WWE.

However, the latest report suggests that Cage has decided to stay with AEW. The Machine made his debut for All Elite Wrestling in 2020, but his talents were not utilized to their fullest potential during his tenure.

According to a report from Fightful Select, several top talents in AEW advocated for Brian Cage to re-sign, and the promotion made a concentrated effort to finalize the deal in the last couple of weeks.

articles.title: "Vince is destroying what Triple H built"
articles.author: Uday Maggon
articles.excerpt: Triple H has taken over WWE creative duties from Vince McMahon for nearly a year now, and the product is noticeably different.
articles.summary:
Triple H has taken over WWE creative duties from Vince McMahon for nearly a year now, and the product is noticeably different. Some feel the latter's recent return to the company cost them signing AEW star Brian Cage.

The Machine was a free agent after his match at Ring of Honor's Supercard of Honor event. The Embassy comprising of Bishop Kaun, Brian Cage, and Toa Liona retained the ROH Six-Man Tag Team Championship by defeating AR Fox, Blake Christian, and Metalik.

It was reported that WWE was interested in the former FTW World Champion.
